h2#sections Page Sections

p
	| In <mark><strong>sem.css</strong></mark>, some special formatting is used
	  in the header and the footer of the page to ease navigation and readability.

h3#header Header <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/header"><code>&lt;header&gt;</code></a>

p
	| Some special styling is applied to the
		<code>&lt;header&gt;</code> tag. When it is the first child of
		<code>&lt;body&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> tag, its heading
		and navigation are styled differently, like the one seen at <a href="#">top of this page</a>.

pre
	| &lt;header&gt;
	    &lt;h1&gt;Header&lt;/h1&gt;
	    &lt;nav&gt;
	      &lt;menu&gt;
	        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#header"&gt;Header&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#footer"&gt;Footer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	      &lt;/menu&gt;
	    &lt;/nav&gt;
	  &lt;/header&gt;

h3#footer Footer <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/footer"><code>&lt;footer&gt;</code></a>

p
	| Like the <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> tag, some special formatting is applied
	  to <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> when it is the last child of
		<code>&lt;body&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> tag. That can also
		been seen at the <a href="#footer">bottom of this page</a>.

pre
	| &lt;footer&gt;
