h2#form Form <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/form"><code>&lt;form&gt;</code></a>

p
	| There is some styling for forms in <mark><strong>sem.css</strong></mark> for the most common controls.
		It works best with the suggested markup below, wrapping every input field into a
		<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/label"><code>&lt;label&gt;</code></a>
		for better usability. However, forms are notorious for how finicky they are with
		styling, accessibility, and inconsistencies between browsers. For anything more complex, as this
		stylesheet is basic, you may need to look for a different styling system better suited
		for your needs.

h3#input Input <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a>

p Works with “textual” input fields like <code>text</code> (the default type) and <code>password</code>.

form[onsubmit="return false" method="post"]
	label
		span Name
		input
		small Enter any name you identifies you best.

pre
	| &lt;label&gt;
	    &lt;span&gt;Name&lt;/span&gt;
	    &lt;input&gt;
	    &lt;small&gt;Enter any name you identifies you best.&lt;/small&gt;
	  &lt;/label&gt;

